         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/6/70 ¶  ¶ The complications in my Department, dear Mr Bentham, have as yet not been solved. This and the heavy duties of the planting season have so fully occcupied my time, that I could only hasti...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.06.17</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 436.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17/6/70</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The complications in my Department, dear Mr Bentham, have as yet not been solved. This and the heavy duties of the planting season have so fully occcupied my time, that I could only hastily pursue the contents of the new proof pages, which you were so good to send me. <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See G. Bentham to M, 15 April 1870.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have made on them a few annotations, and as a whole regard these consecutive treatises as great master-pieces, such as we are accustomed to see emanating from you. Let me also assure you of the appreciation of the generosity, evinced by you, in upholding in so many instances my authorship. The confluence of <name key="Blitum">Blitum</name> with <name key="Chenopodium">Chenopodium</name> through extraeuropean species is interesting,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Bentham (1863-78), vol. 5, pp. 157-8; M united </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Blitum">Blitum</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> with </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Chenopodium">Chenopodium</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style=""> in B69.06.03, p. 11.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> and I contemplate to devote to this subject early more study, as my large universal collection enables me to deal with the question finally. I shall look forward with deep interest to the continuation of the volume. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Trusting your health is quite reestablished and that you enjoy much happiness </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain your very regardful </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">[M] Le Sueur, the excellent Astronomer, who came here last year as observer for the great telescope, has <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">resigned</hi>
               </seg> and returns soon to Europe!<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The PS is written in the margin of the letter. </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Mr [Albert] Le Sueur … has resigned his office as observer in connexion with the telescope, on grounds, however, entirely unconnected with the efficiency or inefficiency of the instrument' (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg> 18 June 1870, p. 1 S). For a history of the Great Melbourne Telescope and the controversies surrounding it, see Gascoigne (1995) and Gillespie (2011).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
